1:04:36.543 --> 1:04:37.544
(GRUNTS IN FRUSTRATION)

1:04:37.628 --> 1:04:38.962
CHAPLAIN:<i> Godspeed to you all.</i>

1:04:39.129 --> 1:04:40.881
And remember...

1:04:41.048 --> 1:04:44.760
<i>"Dulce et decorum
est pro patria mori."</i>

1:04:44.927 --> 1:04:46.053
CADET: What does that mean?

1:04:46.220 --> 1:04:49.014
"It's sweet and proper
to die for one's country."

1:04:49.097 --> 1:04:50.516
(CHIRPING)

1:04:51.808 --> 1:04:53.977
SHOLA: Direct from Germany.

1:04:54.228 --> 1:04:55.229
Thank you.

1:05:01.693 --> 1:05:04.321
LUDENDORFF: (ON RECORDING)
<i>Ja. I am using the cipher.</i>

1:05:04.780 --> 1:05:07.783
<i>Is the eight a "Z" or is it an "R"?</i>

1:05:09.826 --> 1:05:12.454
