with this telegram, old boy.

1:06:10.596 --> 1:06:11.805
Kitchener would be proud.

1:06:13.390 --> 1:06:15.392
Well, I think champagne is in order.

1:06:15.601 --> 1:06:18.478
Uh, thank you, Your Majesty,
but I vowed not to drink

1:06:18.645 --> 1:06:22.733
until Conrad has returned
safely from the war.

1:06:22.900 --> 1:06:24.526
Why didn't you mention that earlier?

1:06:25.068 --> 1:06:27.154
I'll make sure the only action
your boy sees

1:06:27.237 --> 1:06:29.156
is sharpening the general's pencils.

1:06:29.239 --> 1:06:32.618
(LAUGHS) I'm not sure that's cricket.

1:06:36.121 --> 1:06:38.248
Orlando, you know how many
boys' lives you've saved

1:06:38.332 --> 1:06:39.416
with this telegram?

1:06:40.125 --> 1:06:41.835
At least let me save one.

1:06:45.756 --> 1:06:46.757
So,

1:06:47.633 --> 1:06:49.843
now that Conrad's safety is assured...

1:06:52.429 --> 1:06:53.931
to peace in our time.

1:06:54.681 --> 1:06:56.808
To peace in our time.

1:06:58.352 --> 1:07:01.188
AMERICAN GENERAL: King George is waiting
for your response, Mr. President.

1:07:01.355 --> 1:07:03.815
But how can this telegram be real?

1:07:03.982 --> 1:07:05.943
Not even the Germans
would be this stupid.

1:07:06.109 --> 1:07:08.695
-But, sir...
-I'm not doing a damn thing

1:07:08.862 --> 1:07:10.864
till I have undeniable proof.

1:07:11.323 --> 1:07:12.324
Douglas.

1:07:13.116 --> 1:07:15.035
Statesman on the rocks, please.

1:07:16.453 --> 1:07:18.288
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1:07:22.876 --> 1:07:25.337
Lieutenant Oxford reporting
for duty, sir.

1:07:26.505 --> 1:07:28.549
Ah, yes. Oxford.

1:07:29.299 --> 1:07:32.553
Lucky man. You've been
assigned back to London.

1:07:35.305 --> 1:07:37.266
Sir, there must be some mistake.

1:07:37.349 --> 1:07:39.518
No. Fortune favors the brave,

1:07:40.477 --> 1:07:42.646
or those under the king's gaze.

1:07:46.775 --> 1:07:47.943
Sir.

1:07:50.195 --> 1:07:51.238
Attention!

1:08:12.176 --> 1:08:13.260
Lance corporal.

1:08:13.760 --> 1:08:15.637
-Sir.
-What's your name?

1:08:15.804 --> 1:08:17.346
Lance Corporal Reid, sir.

1:08:18.140 --> 1:08:19.140
Follow me.

1:08:35.323 --> 1:08:37.283
Shola, I presume.

1:08:38.702 --> 1:08:39.703
Yes.

1:08:39.870 --> 1:08:42.163
Conrad has sent me to see the duke.

1:08:44.666 --> 1:08:45.667
And your name, sir?

1:08:46.376 --> 1:08:50.839
Good question.
It's a complicated answer.

1:08:51.006 --> 1:08:52.758
I can only tell the duke in person.

1:08:53.133 --> 1:08:54.593
Well, I still need a name.

1:08:54.760 --> 1:08:56.470
This is gonna sound stupid.

1:08:57.179 --> 1:08:59.305
But according to Conrad,
I'm Lancelot.

1:08:59.973 --> 1:09:01.642
You're Merlin,

1:09:01.725 --> 1:09:04.310
and I'm requesting an audience
with King Arthur.

1:09:05.687 --> 1:09:07.272
Follow me, sir.

1:09:10.067 --> 1:09:13.319
OXFORD: "Doubts persist
as to telegram authenticity.

1:09:13.487 --> 1:09:16.240
"Worried Wilson won't go to war."

1:09:16.406 --> 1:09:17.491
Idiots and fools.

1:09:17.573 --> 1:09:19.283
There's nothing left to debate.

1:09:20.702 --> 1:09:23.497
Polly, do you think
we can extend our network

1:09:23.580 --> 1:09:24.581
to the White House?

1:09:25.165 --> 1:09:27.292
Most of their household staff
were trained in England,

1:09:27.376 --> 1:09:28.460
so it shouldn't be a problem.

1:09:28.544 --> 1:09:29.877
Right. Well, let's get to work, then.

1:09:30.045 --> 1:09:32.256
-I'll get on to it right away.
-Thank you.

1:09:36.134 --> 1:09:37.344
(KNOCK AT DOOR)

1:09:38.345 --> 1:09:39.429
Yes, come in.

1:09:41.473 --> 1:09:44.100
Your Grace. We have a visitor.

1:09:44.393 --> 1:09:45.394
Who is it?

1:09:46.019 --> 1:09:48.438
A friend of Conrad
saying he's Lancelot,

1:09:48.604 --> 1:09:50.064
asking to see King Arthur.

1:09:50.232 --> 1:09:52.024
What? (CHUCKLING)

1:09:52.109 --> 1:09:53.902
That brings back fond memories.

1:09:53.986 --> 1:09:55.070
Um...

1:09:55.696 --> 1:09:56.822
Show him in, would you?

1:09:56.989 --> 1:09:57.990
Yes, sir.

1:09:58.866 --> 1:09:59.867
Sir.

1:10:02.452 --> 1:10:03.453
Who are you?

1:10:03.620 --> 1:10:06.373
Lance Corporal Reid
of the Black Watch, sir.

1:10:07.291 --> 1:10:08.375
So then why are you wearing

1:10:08.458 --> 1:10:10.127
a Grenadiers officer's uniform?

1:10:11.128 --> 1:10:12.337
(SIGHS)

1:10:12.754 --> 1:10:13.839
This, uh...

1:10:15.716 --> 1:10:17.885
This will explain it better than I can.

1:10:18.302 --> 1:10:20.220
It's a wee bit surreal, sir.

1:10:25.058 --> 1:10:26.059
OXFORD: Hmm.

1:10:26.727 --> 1:10:27.728
Odd.

1:10:27.978 --> 1:10:30.647
(LAUGHING) It's a letter from Conrad.

1:10:31.815 --> 1:10:33.233
You're Lancelot.

1:10:35.277 --> 1:10:38.488
CONRAD:<i> Dear Father.
I, too, can play games.</i>

1:10:39.615 --> 1:10:42.117
<i>I've swapped places with Archie Reid,</i>

1:10:42.618 --> 1:10:44.036
<i>the man in front of you.</i>

1:10:44.453 --> 1:10:45.454
Archie?

1:10:45.746 --> 1:10:47.414
-CONRAD: <i>He's a good man...
</i>-Yes, sir.

1:10:47.581 --> 1:10:49.458
<i>...who is simply following my orders</i>

1:10:49.541 --> 1:10:52.377
<i>and is possibly
as confused as you are.</i>

1:10:52.794 --> 1:10:54.129
<i>Please ensure my actions</i>

1:10:54.213 --> 1:10:55.839
<i>don't get him into any trouble.</i>

1:10:56.548 --> 1:11:00.010
<i>Tomorrow I finally fulfill
my wish to go to the front.</i>

1:11:00.844 --> 1:11:03.096
<i>And in the meantime,
I enclose a poem</i>

1:11:03.931 --> 1:11:06.058
<i>which I thought
you might appreciate.</i>

1:11:07.559 --> 1:11:08.560
OXFORD: <i>"Bent double...</i>

1:11:10.145 --> 1:11:13.023
<i>"like old beggars under sacks...</i>

1:11:14.733 --> 1:11:18.445
<i>"Knock-kneed,
coughing like hags...</i>

1:11:19.988 --> 1:11:22.491
<i>"we cursed through sludge...</i>

1:11:23.575 --> 1:11:27.746
<i>"Till on the haunting flares
we turned our backs...</i>

1:11:28.872 --> 1:11:34.253
<i>"And towards our distant rest
began to trudge.</i>

1:11:36.713 --> 1:11:38.924
(BAGPIPES PLAYING)

1:11:39.007 --> 1:11:41.426
<i>"Men marched asleep.</i>

1:11:42.594 --> 1:11:46.223
<i>"Many had lost their boots,
but limped on...</i>

1:11:47.015 --> 1:11:48.559
<i>"blood-shod.</i>

1:11:50.394 --> 1:11:54.773
<i>"All went lame, all blind.</i>

1:11:55.816 --> 1:11:58.193
<i>"Drunk with fatigue...</i>

1:11:58.569 --> 1:12:00.654
<i>"deaf even to the hoots...</i>

1:12:00.737 --> 1:12:04.533
<i>"Of tired outstripped five-nines</i>

1:12:04.700 --> 1:12:06.410
<i>"that dropped behind."</i>

1:12:07.286 --> 1:12:08.704
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

1:12:14.251 --> 1:12:15.252
SERGEANT MAJOR: New lads.

1:12:15.586 --> 1:12:16.879
Welcome to the front line.

1:12:17.045 --> 1:12:18.338
This trench will be your home
for the next six...

1:12:18.422 --> 1:12:20.966
I don't bloody believe it. Runner!

1:12:21.884 --> 1:12:23.343
SERGEANT MAJOR: Come on, lads!

1:12:25.637 --> 1:12:27.472
(GUNFIRE AND EXPLOSIONS)

1:12:33.770 --> 1:12:36.023
Well, come on, lads! Cover the man!

1:12:38.317 --> 1:12:40.319
Cover the man!

1:12:43.989 --> 1:12:45.157
Fire!

1:12:45.240 --> 1:12:46.575
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1:12:46.658 --> 1:12:47.743
Keep running!

1:12:53.665 --> 1:12:55.250
SERGEANT MAJOR: Hold your fire!

1:13:01.548 --> 1:13:02.883
Good effort, men.

1:13:03.759 --> 1:13:06.053
This war never stops surprising me.

1:13:06.470 --> 1:13:09.890
A German wavin' a Union Jack!
What's next?

1:13:10.682 --> 1:13:12.351
CAPTAIN FORREST: Allow me
to answer that, Sergeant Major.

1:13:12.518 --> 1:13:13.936
SERGEANT MAJOR: Fall in!

1:13:16.772 --> 1:13:19.399
That runner was actually a British spy.

1:13:19.566 --> 1:13:21.235
He was bringing me vital information.

1:13:21.902 --> 1:13:23.195
Our country needs
what he was carrying,

1:13:23.278 --> 1:13:25.489
and I therefore need six volunteers.

1:13:26.114 --> 1:13:28.075
You will accompany me
to retrieve what's left of him

1:13:28.158 --> 1:13:30.244
as soon as it's dark.

1:13:34.081 --> 1:13:35.249
Very good, lad.

1:13:36.625 --> 1:13:37.709
Who else?

1:13:39.837 --> 1:13:40.879
Sergeant?

1:13:42.172 --> 1:13:45.008
You five. One step forward. March!

1:13:46.969 --> 1:13:49.054
Five more brave volunteers, sir.

1:13:49.221 --> 1:13:52.683
Excellent. We move out at midnight.

1:14:00.607 --> 1:14:02.442
(RATS SQUEAKING)

1:14:26.175 --> 1:14:28.010
(FAINT RUSTLING)

1:14:33.432 --> 1:14:34.600
(WHISPERING) Hold your fire.

1:14:35.392 --> 1:14:36.768
If they hear us from the trenches,

1:14:36.852 --> 1:14:39.271
we'll be fired upon from both sides.

1:14:48.280 --> 1:14:49.281
(SHUSHES SOFTLY)

1:14:54.453 --> 1:14:56.163
(WHISPERS) Boom.

1:15:43.544 --> 1:15:45.379
(ALL GRUNTING)

1:16:02.187 --> 1:16:03.188
(MUFFLED SCREAMING)

1:16:12.281 --> 1:16:13.490
TROOPER: Please...

1:16:14.741 --> 1:16:16.535
-Please don't.
-(MAN GROANING)

1:16:21.123 --> 1:16:22.958
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1:16:27.171 --> 1:16:28.755
(TROOPER MUTTERING INDISTINCTLY)

1:16:30.632 --> 1:16:31.717
I'm so sorry.

1:16:31.800 --> 1:16:32.885
(GROANS)

1:16:33.635 --> 1:16:35.637
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1:16:38.765 --> 1:16:40.601
(ALL GRUNTING)

1:17:01.580 --> 1:17:02.789
-(CLANGS)
-(GASPS)

1:17:02.873 --> 1:17:03.874
What was that?

1:17:03.957 --> 1:17:06.168
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1:17:28.357 --> 1:17:29.358
(IN ENGLISH) It's over there.

1:17:29.441 --> 1:17:30.859
CONRAD: Don't shoot!

1:17:31.860 --> 1:17:33.028
(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1:17:33.111 --> 1:17:34.112
No!

1:17:39.159 --> 1:17:40.661
(PANTING)

1:17:54.842 --> 1:17:56.134
(YELLING)

1:17:57.427 --> 1:17:58.428
(YELLING)

1:18:09.481 --> 1:18:11.900
-(GUNFIRE CONTINUES)
-(INDISTINCT SHOUTING)

1:18:13.986 --> 1:18:16.280
-(COUGHING)
-BRITISH SOLDIER: Cease fire!

1:18:22.744 --> 1:18:24.580
(PANTING HEAVILY)

1:18:29.751 --> 1:18:31.587
(SOBBING)

1:18:41.138 --> 1:18:42.723
MAN: First time out here, lad?

1:18:43.807 --> 1:18:45.475
Hey. Whoa, whoa, whoa.

1:18:47.561 --> 1:18:48.979
Same side.

1:18:49.771 --> 1:18:51.398
Thank God for the Union Jack, eh?

1:18:55.777 --> 1:18:57.779
I can honestly say that my first time

1:18:57.863 --> 1:18:59.615
was worse than losing this leg. (CHUCKLES)

1:19:02.451 --> 1:19:05.746
I'm so sorry, I shouldn't
be the one crying.

1:19:06.038 --> 1:19:08.540
Come over here and help me out.
I'm freezing.

1:19:14.379 --> 1:19:17.257
Come here. Come on.

1:19:17.591 --> 1:19:19.218
(SHUSHING)

1:19:20.511 --> 1:19:22.346
(CONRAD CONTINUES SOBBING)

1:19:25.474 --> 1:19:29.353
I thought... I thought I knew
what I wanted.

1:19:35.484 --> 1:19:37.736
My father warned me.

1:19:38.820 --> 1:19:42.032
My father warned me.
I... I didn't listen...

1:19:43.534 --> 1:19:45.827
and now it all makes sense.

1:19:49.998 --> 1:19:52.751
I didn't even get to say goodbye.

1:19:53.669 --> 1:19:57.798
Well, I suggest we solve
both our problems, yeah?

1:19:58.423 --> 1:19:59.883
Look.

1:20:00.634 --> 1:20:02.636
I need to get this
to high command.

1:20:03.053 --> 1:20:05.639
The contents could help
end this bloody war.

1:20:06.598 --> 1:20:09.893
As I won't be walking
any time soon,

1:20:11.186 --> 1:20:13.981
I suggest you finish the mission

1:20:16.191 --> 1:20:18.318
and go home to a hero's welcome.

1:20:18.861 --> 1:20:23.740
No, no. No. Off we go
to a hero's welcome.

1:20:43.927 --> 1:20:46.096
-(WHIMPERING)
-It's okay. I've got you.

1:20:51.101 --> 1:20:52.269
(SPEAKING GERMAN)

1:20:55.355 --> 1:20:57.399
Shit. Hurry!

1:20:59.610 --> 1:21:01.737
BRITISH SOLDIER: Covering fire!

1:21:01.904 --> 1:21:03.197
Give them cover, lads!

1:21:06.617 --> 1:21:07.618
Fucking move!

1:21:09.161 --> 1:21:11.288
(YELLING)

1:21:11.371 --> 1:21:13.207
Take out the machine gunner!

1:21:13.665 --> 1:21:14.917
SOLDIER: Cover him!

1:21:20.589 --> 1:21:23.133
Go!

1:21:23.300 --> 1:21:26.053
Run!

1:21:26.220 --> 1:21:28.514
SOLDIER 1: Let's go, man! Run!
SOLDIER 2: Run! Run! Run!

1:22:08.011 --> 1:22:10.055
You all right? You all right?

1:22:10.597 --> 1:22:12.891
Jesus Christ! You were amazin'!

1:22:12.975 --> 1:22:14.768
I've never seen anything like it.

1:22:14.935 --> 1:22:16.270
What the bloody hell
were you doing over there

1:22:16.353 --> 1:22:17.396
in the first place?

1:22:17.479 --> 1:22:18.772
(PANTING)

1:22:18.856 --> 1:22:20.941
You better ask him. Ask him.

1:22:21.400 --> 1:22:23.318
He'll explain everything.

1:22:24.403 --> 1:22:26.029
SOLDIER: He took the full force
of that blast, sir.

1:22:26.196 --> 1:22:28.448
Yeah. But at least
you made it back, son.

1:22:29.032 --> 1:22:31.743
I tell you, if that ain't worth
a Victoria Cross,

1:22:31.827 --> 1:22:32.828
I don't know what is.

1:22:32.995 --> 1:22:34.413
I must carry on the mission.

1:22:34.580 --> 1:22:36.790
We need to get this
to high command immediately.

1:22:36.957 --> 1:22:39.877
I'll take you there myself.
What's your name, soldier?

1:22:41.003 --> 1:22:43.964
Archie. Lance Corporal Archie Reid.

1:22:44.131 --> 1:22:45.132
SERGEANT MAJOR ATKINS:
Archie Reid, did you say?

1:22:46.800 --> 1:22:47.801
Yes.

1:22:48.218 --> 1:22:49.303
That's right.

1:22:49.469 --> 1:22:50.971
Lance Corporal Archie Reid?

1:22:51.847 --> 1:22:54.016
Dog Platoon, First Battalion,
the Black Watch?

1:22:54.850 --> 1:22:55.851
Aye.

1:22:58.145 --> 1:22:59.938
Is that your best Scottish accent?

1:23:00.522 --> 1:23:01.523
You're not Archie Reid.

1:23:02.149 --> 1:23:04.151
Lance Corporal Archie Reid's
a friend of mine.

1:23:04.234 --> 1:23:06.028
And I've been looking for him all night.
So who are you?

1:23:06.111 --> 1:23:10.157
Yes, yes. You're right.
There's a simple explanation.

1:23:10.657 --> 1:23:11.992
-I'm not Archie Reid.
-Fuckin' German spy.

1:23:12.159 --> 1:23:13.243
I'm Conra...

1:23:34.723 --> 1:23:36.350
REID: <i>Your son was killed in action, sir.</i>

1:23:49.446 --> 1:23:50.447
OXFORD: What?

1:24:24.022 --> 1:24:25.524
(SOBBING)

1:24:33.907 --> 1:24:34.992
Polly.

1:24:38.412 --> 1:24:39.580
Polly.

1:24:51.508 --> 1:24:53.093
My son.

1:25:03.353 --> 1:25:04.813
Why?

1:25:16.700 --> 1:25:20.746
<i>"If in some
smothering dreams...</i>

1:25:20.913 --> 1:25:22.706
<i>"you too could pace</i>

1:25:22.789 --> 1:25:25.542
<i>"Behind the wagon
that we flung him in...</i>

1:25:26.376 --> 1:25:30.881
<i>"And watch the white eyes
writhing in his face...</i>

1:25:33.509 --> 1:25:38.805
"His hanging face,
like a devil's sick of sin...

1:25:39.431 --> 1:25:42.726
"If you could hear, at every jolt...

1:25:43.018 --> 1:25:47.272
"the blood, come gargling
from the froth-corrupted lungs...

1:25:48.649 --> 1:25:51.235
"Obscene as cancer...

1:25:52.277 --> 1:25:54.321
"bitter as the cud...

1:25:54.696 --> 1:26:00.285
"Of vile, incurable sores
on innocent tongues...

1:26:01.453 --> 1:26:02.829
"My friend...

1:26:03.956 --> 1:26:08.168
"you would not tell
with such high zest...

1:26:08.335 --> 1:26:11.046
"To children ardent for...

1:26:11.713 --> 1:26:13.882
"some desperate glory...

1:26:14.049 --> 1:26:15.926
"The old Lie...

1:26:17.386 --> 1:26:20.430
<i>"Dulce et decorum est...</i>

1:26:21.515 --> 1:26:24.101
<i>"Pro patria mori."</i>

1:26:25.978 --> 1:26:29.022
It is sweet and proper

1:26:29.898 --> 1:26:33.277
to die for one's country.

1:26:50.836 --> 1:26:54.298
I, Nikolai Aleksandrovich Romanov,

1:26:54.464 --> 1:26:56.508
Emperor of Russia,

1:26:56.675 --> 1:26:59.011
do hereby declare
my irrevocable determination

1:26:59.178 --> 1:27:01.263
to renounce the throne for myself

1:27:01.346 --> 1:27:02.347
and my descendants

1:27:02.514 --> 1:27:05.851
through this instrument
of abdication...

1:27:07.686 --> 1:27:09.229
immediately.

1:27:17.613 --> 1:27:19.573
ALL: Hurrah! Hurrah! Hurrah!

1:27:35.589 --> 1:27:37.674
(SOFTLY) The documents
Conrad recovered

1:27:38.425 --> 1:27:40.302
turned out to be
the German ambassador's

1:27:40.385 --> 1:27:43.639
original handwritten telegram
that I cracked.

1:27:44.640 --> 1:27:47.267
It's the concrete proof America needed.

1:27:47.893 --> 1:27:50.729
SHOLA: America will now
have to join the war.

1:27:51.063 --> 1:27:54.024
Conrad succeeded where we all failed.

1:27:57.528 --> 1:27:59.530
-(SWORDS CLANGING)
-(MEN GRUNTING)

1:28:04.868 --> 1:28:05.994
ERIK: My Shepherd.

1:28:07.287 --> 1:28:08.664
SHEPHERD: There is a code of honor

1:28:09.039 --> 1:28:11.834
and using a distraction
to your own advantage

1:28:11.917 --> 1:28:13.502
breaks that code.

1:28:13.669 --> 1:28:15.295
-What?
-Apologies, my Shepherd,

1:28:15.379 --> 1:28:17.297
but I have disturbing news.

1:28:17.464 --> 1:28:20.592
While your plan for Russia
has been a great success,

1:28:20.801 --> 1:28:24.555
my plan to keep America
out of the war has backfired.

1:28:25.180 --> 1:28:26.390
The American president

1:28:26.473 --> 1:28:28.183
is about to be given
the actual telegram

1:28:28.267 --> 1:28:29.768
I forced the kaiser to send.

1:28:30.143 --> 1:28:31.728
Such undeniable proof

1:28:31.812 --> 1:28:34.398
could provoke the Americans
into entering the war.

1:28:35.607 --> 1:28:37.109
(GOATS BLEATING)

1:28:39.820 --> 1:28:41.154
SHEPHERD:<i> En garde.</i>

1:28:46.785 --> 1:28:50.080
I like a man who will admit
to his mistakes, I do.

1:28:50.539 --> 1:28:54.543
But I like more a woman
who can fix them.

1:28:54.877 --> 1:28:57.171
Have our American friend Dupont

1:28:57.296 --> 1:28:59.548
get Mata into the White House.

1:28:59.715 --> 1:29:01.758
Time for you to work your magic

1:29:01.842 --> 1:29:04.011
on the president, Mata.

1:29:04.178 --> 1:29:05.554
Now, go on.

1:29:06.638 --> 1:29:08.557
It's time to show the president

1:29:09.057 --> 1:29:11.560
who the real boss is.

1:29:21.153 --> 1:29:22.571
Will Your Grace be having tea?

1:29:25.949 --> 1:29:27.784
It's scotch time.

1:29:28.619 --> 1:29:30.287
Twenty-four hours a day.

1:29:41.340 --> 1:29:42.549
(DOOR CLOSES)

1:30:07.491 --> 1:30:08.992
-(KNOCK ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS)
-For the last time,

1:30:09.076 --> 1:30:10.577
I don't want any fucking tea!

1:30:10.744 --> 1:30:12.120
Neither do I.

1:30:13.664 --> 1:30:14.831
OXFORD: Sir.

1:30:17.793 --> 1:30:20.963
Though it looks like you could
use a strong one to sober up.

1:30:22.381 --> 1:30:24.341
I'm afraid it'll take
more than that, sir.

1:30:24.508 --> 1:30:26.802
Oh, well, maybe this
will do the trick.

1:30:26.969 --> 1:30:28.971
Russia's pulled
out of the war.

1:30:29.638 --> 1:30:32.140
The British Empire faces imminent defeat.

1:30:32.891 --> 1:30:35.519
America still refuses to join.

1:30:36.562 --> 1:30:39.481
I personally telephoned
President Wilson.

1:30:40.899 --> 1:30:42.985
He didn't deign to receive my call.

1:30:43.235 --> 1:30:45.904
Hmm. So, they got to him as well.

1:30:46.071 --> 1:30:47.573
-KING GEORGE: Indeed.
-Hmm.

1:30:48.615 --> 1:30:50.617
The kaiser's blockade is working.

1:30:51.368 --> 1:30:53.120
The people are hungry.

1:30:53.871 --> 1:30:56.957
The next revolution might be here.

1:30:58.500 --> 1:31:01.044
I've even been advised
to change my German surname

1:31:01.128 --> 1:31:03.714
Saxe-Coburg to Windsor.

1:31:04.339 --> 1:31:05.507
More English.

1:31:05.799 --> 1:31:07.217
(SCOFFING)

1:31:08.093 --> 1:31:09.970
I'm afraid, then, sir,

1:31:10.512 --> 1:31:12.556
that England is doomed.

1:31:19.980 --> 1:31:21.607
I wanted to give you this.

1:31:23.108 --> 1:31:24.151
For Conrad.

1:31:24.902 --> 1:31:27.529
A true hero.

1:31:29.656 --> 1:31:32.075
A man who knew his duty.

1:31:43.337 --> 1:31:46.757
Enough of this self-pitying poppycock.

1:31:47.424 --> 1:31:48.675
If it were just you...

1:31:49.218 --> 1:31:53.472
you and I, in our grief,
I'd say do as you will.

1:31:53.889 --> 1:31:57.309
Drown in drink, and I'd join you.

1:31:58.477 --> 1:32:00.020
But he's watching.

1:32:02.439 --> 1:32:05.150
And he would have been
such a better man.

1:32:09.530 --> 1:32:11.073
But he can't.

1:32:12.282 --> 1:32:16.119
He won't be that. Not anymore.

1:32:16.620 --> 1:32:20.916
So, you must, in his stead,

1:32:22.501 --> 1:32:25.504
be the man your son
would have been.

1:32:32.386 --> 1:32:35.347
Regretfully, I can no longer
remain in your service.

1:32:37.224 --> 1:32:38.684
Forgive me, my lady.

1:32:47.484 --> 1:32:49.528
My heart is broken as well.

1:32:50.571 --> 1:32:52.948
Polly. Polly.

1:32:53.615 --> 1:32:54.825
(OPENS DOOR)

1:32:54.908 --> 1:32:56.785
I do not accept your resignation.

1:32:59.413 --> 1:33:00.455
But...

1:33:01.874 --> 1:33:05.919
I will accept a very strong cup of tea.

1:33:39.036 --> 1:33:40.162
Looking better, Your Grace.

1:33:42.122 --> 1:33:43.832
Feeling better, Polly.

1:33:45.751 --> 1:33:46.960
So, what have I missed?

1:33:47.461 --> 1:33:49.755
We followed your last sober order

1:33:49.922 --> 1:33:52.966
<i>and extended our network
to the White House.</i>

1:33:53.133 --> 1:33:54.843
<i>The president's butler informed us</i>

1:33:54.927 --> 1:33:57.221
<i>that since receiving
the telegram Conrad recovered,</i>

1:33:57.429 --> 1:33:59.348
<i>the president hasn't been himself.</i>

1:33:59.515 --> 1:34:01.558
This may be the proof I asked for.

1:34:01.642 --> 1:34:03.101
But remember my election promise.

1:34:03.268 --> 1:34:04.853
Out of the war, not in.

1:34:05.020 --> 1:34:07.356
Douglas, get me a Statesman
on the rocks, now!

1:34:07.439 --> 1:34:09.024
-(PHONE RINGS)
-POLLY: <i>Constantly engaged</i>

1:34:09.107 --> 1:34:11.777
<i>in top-secret conversations
with his embassy in London.</i>

1:34:11.944 --> 1:34:14.196
And ignoring all advice
to go to war.

1:34:14.363 --> 1:34:16.448
And do we have someone
in the embassy?

1:34:16.615 --> 1:34:17.783
Of course.

1:34:18.242 --> 1:34:19.326
MAN: Mr. President...

1:34:19.701 --> 1:34:21.078
I don't know how to proceed.

1:34:21.286 --> 1:34:23.789
<i>We're meeting to discuss
her new demands.</i>

1:34:23.956 --> 1:34:25.415
-I see.
-She was very convincing.

1:34:25.582 --> 1:34:28.502
And she suggests we make
an unannounced visit at 3:00.

1:34:28.669 --> 1:34:32.130
Right, well. We had better
get a move on, then.

1:34:46.353 --> 1:34:47.521
OXFORD: Good afternoon.

1:34:47.604 --> 1:34:48.939
Please inform the ambassador

1:34:49.022 --> 1:34:50.899
the Duke of Oxford
is here to see him.

1:34:52.693 --> 1:34:53.902
Yes, Your Grace.

1:34:54.194 --> 1:34:55.404
(KNOCK ON DOOR, DOOR OPENS)

1:34:55.487 --> 1:34:56.905
Mr. Ambassador.

1:34:56.989 --> 1:34:58.490
(CONTINUES SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY)

1:35:02.744 --> 1:35:03.912
OXFORD: <i>Why did you kill my friend?</i>

1:35:04.413 --> 1:35:05.706
It was the alcohol.

1:35:06.039 --> 1:35:07.040
I was overcome.

1:35:08.333 --> 1:35:10.377
MATA: <i>Thank you for your time,
Mr. Ambassador.</i>

1:35:13.922 --> 1:35:15.048
Hmm.

1:35:17.718 --> 1:35:19.678
If you wouldn't mind...

1:35:20.470 --> 1:35:23.724
I'm sorry. I couldn't help
admiring your scarf.

1:35:23.891 --> 1:35:25.601
An exquisite cashmere.

1:35:25.767 --> 1:35:27.144
Yes, it's very rare.

1:35:27.227 --> 1:35:30.230
Hmm. Do you know the test
of a truly pure cashmere?

1:35:31.565 --> 1:35:32.858
-A ring.
-Mmm-hmm.

1:35:33.066 --> 1:35:37.112
Yet, happily, you do not wear one.

1:35:37.779 --> 1:35:39.740
You are

1:35:41.116 --> 1:35:42.159
mistaken.

1:35:42.534 --> 1:35:43.911
Now that

1:35:45.120 --> 1:35:46.246
is disappointing.

1:35:46.413 --> 1:35:48.081
But this

1:35:49.499 --> 1:35:50.501
is not.

1:35:57.174 --> 1:35:59.009
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1:36:02.804 --> 1:36:04.556
I believe it's ungentlemanly
to hurt a woman,

1:36:04.723 --> 1:36:05.933
but since the fate of the world

1:36:06.016 --> 1:36:07.976
hangs in the balance,
I'm going to bend the rules.

1:36:08.143 --> 1:36:09.311
Now tell me who's behind this,

1:36:09.394 --> 1:36:12.189
or so help me
you'll never breathe again.

1:36:13.357 --> 1:36:15.150
You will have to kill me.

1:36:25.118 --> 1:36:27.412
Ah... Ambassador.

1:36:29.164 --> 1:36:30.916
-Is she dead?
-No.

1:36:31.333 --> 1:36:33.836
She has an extreme case
of hypoxia.

1:36:34.127 --> 1:36:36.129
She'll be fine, and so will you,

1:36:36.213 --> 1:36:38.924
as long as we have
an honest conversation.

1:36:46.723 --> 1:36:48.058
AMBASSADOR:
What you're lookin' at

1:36:48.141 --> 1:36:50.102
is the lady you strangled.

1:36:50.519 --> 1:36:53.188
She filmed herself
seducing the president

1:36:53.272 --> 1:36:54.982
and is now blackmailing us

1:36:55.065 --> 1:36:57.734
to not even think
about entering the war.

1:36:57.985 --> 1:37:01.613
We cannot risk the integrity
of the U.S. presidency.

1:37:01.697 --> 1:37:03.073
I'm sure.

1:37:03.323 --> 1:37:06.076
Now, if we can get that negative,

1:37:06.159 --> 1:37:08.078
then we will happily join England

1:37:08.161 --> 1:37:10.038
and put Germany out of business.

1:37:10.122 --> 1:37:12.416
Well, I suggest
you interrogate her.

1:37:12.916 --> 1:37:16.753
And I'll follow up on this.

1:37:18.714 --> 1:37:21.758
This is cashmere
from the Kamaliro goat.

1:37:22.843 --> 1:37:23.886
It's very rare.

1:37:24.553 --> 1:37:25.721
Where does it come from?

1:37:26.513 --> 1:37:29.224
Mr. Collins,
cashmere book number one, please.

1:37:31.560 --> 1:37:32.561
Thank you.

1:37:33.896 --> 1:37:36.481
It comes from here.

1:37:36.648 --> 1:37:38.192
The only place in the world

1:37:38.275 --> 1:37:40.277
where the Kamaliro goat breeds.

1:37:40.444 --> 1:37:42.446
OXFORD: Excellent. Shola,

1:37:42.946 --> 1:37:45.449
we're going
into the cashmere business.

1:38:03.175 --> 1:38:06.470
I can see six men guarding the lift.

1:38:07.262 --> 1:38:08.555
Ah...

1:38:08.639 --> 1:38:09.806
If you can call it that.

1:38:09.973 --> 1:38:12.851
Give the word and their numbers
will be reduced.

1:38:13.560 --> 1:38:14.561
Oh, no, Polly.

1:38:14.645 --> 1:38:16.897
The film's negative
is going to be up there.

1:38:17.064 --> 1:38:18.440
And that's our real prize.

1:38:18.607 --> 1:38:19.775
If these guards are alerted,

1:38:19.858 --> 1:38:21.568
then I don't think we'll make it up.

1:38:21.735 --> 1:38:23.862
It's vital that we control this lift.

1:38:29.493 --> 1:38:32.829
This is called a parachute.

1:38:33.288 --> 1:38:36.208
It means that one can jump
out of a plane safely.

1:38:37.709 --> 1:38:38.710
So,

1:38:39.503 --> 1:38:42.005
tomorrow at dawn I'll fly
the plane over the mountain

1:38:42.089 --> 1:38:43.590
and Shola will jump out.

1:38:44.258 --> 1:38:46.218
You land with the parachute,

1:38:46.385 --> 1:38:50.931
take control of the lift,
and then you fire this flare.

1:38:51.348 --> 1:38:52.766
It's a signal to me,

1:38:52.850 --> 1:38:54.726
by which time
I'll have landed the plane,

1:38:54.893 --> 1:38:57.062
made my way over
to the bottom of the lift,

1:38:57.145 --> 1:38:58.689
while Polly provides cover.

1:38:59.523 --> 1:39:02.442
Sir, I could do anything for you,

1:39:02.609 --> 1:39:05.112
but I cannot jump out of an airplane.

1:39:05.487 --> 1:39:07.322
And it's not that I wouldn't try,

1:39:08.615 --> 1:39:10.784
it's that I know I'd let you down.

1:39:11.618 --> 1:39:14.121
Yes. Well, I appreciate
your fear of heights,

1:39:14.288 --> 1:39:17.541
but I am the only one
who can fly. So...

1:39:17.833 --> 1:39:19.626
But you wouldn't
have to land the plane.

1:39:19.793 --> 1:39:22.004
You just have to land yourself.

1:39:23.672 --> 1:39:26.091
Hmm. Well, it, um...

1:39:27.134 --> 1:39:29.720
It would be bad form to ask
a man to do something

1:39:29.803 --> 1:39:32.055
that I wouldn't do myself.

1:39:32.222 --> 1:39:36.059
All right, Shola,
get ready for my signal.

1:39:37.519 --> 1:39:39.021
We go at dawn.

1:40:10.636 --> 1:40:12.137
(ENGINE STOPS)

1:40:25.442 --> 1:40:26.860
(SCREAMING)

1:40:29.112 --> 1:40:30.948
(GRUNTING)

1:40:51.260 --> 1:40:52.469
(GRUNTING)

1:40:55.931 --> 1:40:57.057
(YELLING)

1:41:07.359 --> 1:41:08.569
(SCREAMS)

1:41:22.916 --> 1:41:24.126
Whoa.

1:41:26.587 --> 1:41:28.422
(GOATS BLEATING)

1:41:39.349 --> 1:41:40.434
(GRUNTING)

1:41:44.646 --> 1:41:46.481
(WIND HOWLING)

1:41:49.568 --> 1:41:50.986
(BLEATING)

1:41:52.613 --> 1:41:53.614
(GROANS)

1:41:58.202 --> 1:41:59.286
Oh...

1:42:21.266 --> 1:42:22.768
(GRUNTING)

1:43:02.975 --> 1:43:04.476
(GOAT BLEATING)

1:43:12.985 --> 1:43:14.069
(GRUNTS)

1:43:14.152 --> 1:43:15.654
(PANTING)

1:43:30.919 --> 1:43:32.754
(GOATS BLEATING)

1:43:36.300 --> 1:43:37.718
(RUMBLING)

1:43:41.430 --> 1:43:42.431
Shit!

1:43:52.274 --> 1:43:54.109
(GROWLING)

1:43:57.613 --> 1:43:58.822
-(BLEATS)
-Oh!

1:44:15.547 --> 1:44:16.965
(HUFFS)

1:44:19.343 --> 1:44:22.804
Shh. That's it. That's it.

1:44:34.525 --> 1:44:36.401
SHEPHERD:
Answer the question, Dupont.

1:44:36.568 --> 1:44:39.446
Do you know where Mata is?

1:44:39.613 --> 1:44:40.614
DUPONT: No. I...

1:44:40.697 --> 1:44:42.699
SHEPHERD: Well, you fuckin' should.

1:44:42.866 --> 1:44:45.244
Because I sent her
to the American Embassy,

1:44:45.327 --> 1:44:47.871
and she hasn't been
seen since! (GRUNTS)

1:44:49.540 --> 1:44:50.916
Do you see this?

1:44:51.083 --> 1:44:54.586
If the American president
thinks he can fuck me too,

1:44:54.753 --> 1:44:56.588
he is very much mistaken.

1:44:56.755 --> 1:44:59.174
Take this negative to the press,

1:44:59.258 --> 1:45:01.593
and it will ruin his reputation.

1:45:01.760 --> 1:45:05.430
War will be the last thing
on the Americans' mind.

1:45:05.597 --> 1:45:07.432
And when the scandal is over,

1:45:07.516 --> 1:45:10.894
make sure the new president
is in our pocket!

1:45:11.103 --> 1:45:13.063
Go on. Run! Run!

1:45:13.438 --> 1:45:14.982
All the way to the White House.

1:45:21.029 --> 1:45:22.239
Let's check the other side.

1:45:22.406 --> 1:45:24.116
Let's go around to the south.

1:45:26.702 --> 1:45:28.912
Make it snappy, pal!

1:45:35.335 --> 1:45:36.336
Hey!

1:45:43.719 --> 1:45:45.345
What the hell?

1:45:46.388 --> 1:45:47.598
(GRUNTING)

1:45:49.224 --> 1:45:50.726
-(GRUNTS)
-(YELPS)

1:45:51.226 --> 1:45:52.311
(ROARS)

1:45:52.394 --> 1:45:53.854
Buddy, what's the holdup?

1:45:53.937 --> 1:45:56.648
(GROWLING)

1:46:02.237 --> 1:46:03.238
Look!

1:46:04.031 --> 1:46:05.199
POLLY: There's the signal.

1:46:05.407 --> 1:46:07.743
Get to the lift. I'll cover you.

1:46:10.704 --> 1:46:11.955
(FIRES GUN)

1:46:12.039 --> 1:46:13.916
(SCREAMING)

1:46:13.999 --> 1:46:15.834
-(ROARS)
-(GRUNTS)

1:46:21.131 --> 1:46:22.132
Up on the hill!

1:46:23.967 --> 1:46:25.093
(YELLS)

1:46:39.024 --> 1:46:40.192
(YELLING)

1:46:45.030 --> 1:46:46.240
(GRUNTS)

1:46:47.157 --> 1:46:49.076
(GRUNTING)

1:46:51.453 --> 1:46:53.205
(YELLING)

1:46:59.962 --> 1:47:01.129
(YELLING)

1:47:14.268 --> 1:47:15.477
(YELLING)

1:47:17.229 --> 1:47:18.438
(GROWLS)

1:47:19.022 --> 1:47:20.357
(GRUNTS)

1:47:23.569 --> 1:47:26.071
Who the hell is that guy?

1:47:26.154 --> 1:47:27.948
(SCREAMING)

1:47:28.031 --> 1:47:29.366
(GRUNTING)

1:47:36.748 --> 1:47:38.083
(GUNSHOT)

1:47:40.252 --> 1:47:42.129
(LAUGHING)

1:47:46.592 --> 1:47:50.679
Shola! Stop fuckin' about!
Get on that counterweight!

1:47:58.812 --> 1:48:00.314
(YELLS)

1:48:05.319 --> 1:48:07.029
Oh, fuck!

1:48:07.696 --> 1:48:08.697
Oh...

1:48:08.780 --> 1:48:10.657
(SCREAMING)

1:48:16.622 --> 1:48:17.831
(SCREAMING)

1:48:19.875 --> 1:48:21.793
(GROANING)

1:48:35.140 --> 1:48:37.559
OXFORD: (SIGHS IN RELIEF)
Thank God you're here.

1:48:38.602 --> 1:48:41.480
This plan hasn't exactly gone
by the numbers.

1:48:43.232 --> 1:48:45.067
(PHONE RINGING)

1:48:47.736 --> 1:48:49.530
Polly. Do you have the film?

1:48:49.696 --> 1:48:51.823
I have the negative
in my hand, Your Grace.

1:48:52.407 --> 1:48:53.742
Well done.

1:48:53.909 --> 1:48:55.536
So we have what we came for.

1:48:55.619 --> 1:48:58.956
Yes. But the cause of all this mayhem
is still in there.

1:48:59.289 --> 1:49:01.834
Enough of dealing
with tentacles, Shola.

1:49:02.000 --> 1:49:03.752
It's time to cut off the head.

1:49:04.586 --> 1:49:06.380
It's good to have you back, sir.

1:49:11.218 --> 1:49:12.719
(MEN CLAMORING)

1:49:12.803 --> 1:49:14.054
(ALL GRUNTING)

1:49:35.576 --> 1:49:37.578
(DOOR CREAKING)

1:49:45.377 --> 1:49:46.378
(GUNFIRE)

1:50:01.685 --> 1:50:06.064
SHEPHERD: You have got to be
fucking kidding me.

1:50:06.315 --> 1:50:08.525
The thorn in my side

1:50:08.609 --> 1:50:12.446
has just been
a peace-loving English rose.

1:50:13.071 --> 1:50:17.034
The Duke of Oxford.
Good day to you, sir!

1:50:17.993 --> 1:50:19.786
You are the very symbol

1:50:19.953 --> 1:50:22.164
of everything I'm tryin' to destroy.

1:50:22.331 --> 1:50:24.082
Aristocrats like you

1:50:24.166 --> 1:50:27.461
stole my parents' mill
in Scotland when I was a lad.

1:50:27.920 --> 1:50:31.632
Entitlement has "title" in it
for a reason, no? Huh!

1:50:32.925 --> 1:50:36.094
I'm gonna fucking love
killing you.

1:50:36.261 --> 1:50:38.972
Come to papa, you posh prick!

1:50:50.025 --> 1:50:51.026
I'm out.

1:50:59.368 --> 1:51:00.577
(GUN CLICKING)

1:51:02.246 --> 1:51:03.372
(GUN CLICKING)

1:51:07.793 --> 1:51:10.546
SHEPHERD: The sound of silence.

1:51:11.255 --> 1:51:14.758
It's my understanding that you, Duke,

1:51:14.842 --> 1:51:16.927
are a formidable swordsman.

1:51:17.719 --> 1:51:22.891
What say we end this shite
as gentlemen?

1:51:23.892 --> 1:51:25.143
After all,

1:51:25.686 --> 1:51:28.105
manners maketh man.

1:51:28.814 --> 1:51:32.025
A gentleman does not hide
in the shadows.

1:51:33.193 --> 1:51:34.194
SHEPHERD: Aye.

1:51:47.124 --> 1:51:48.750
(IN ENGLISH ACCENT) Surprise.

1:51:57.050 --> 1:51:58.260
Morton.

1:51:59.970 --> 1:52:00.971
You see,

1:52:01.638 --> 1:52:02.764
<i>a little misplaced trust</i>

1:52:02.848 --> 1:52:04.892
<i>allows one to get away with murder.</i>

1:52:05.058 --> 1:52:08.228
This debate should happen
after we have won the war.

1:52:09.563 --> 1:52:13.150
I suggest we go to Russia,
and we sort it out ourselves.

1:52:13.317 --> 1:52:14.943
<i>And in poor Kitchener's case,</i>

1:52:17.446 --> 1:52:18.906
<i>quite literally.</i>

1:52:22.743 --> 1:52:24.203
Spoken like a true traitor.

1:52:24.661 --> 1:52:27.122
(IN NORMAL ACCENT)
As far as I'm concerned, his blood...

1:52:28.123 --> 1:52:29.208
(SPITS)

1:52:30.250 --> 1:52:32.544
...that's on your grubby hands.

1:52:35.088 --> 1:52:36.256
Two on one?

1:52:37.090 --> 1:52:39.468
Behaving like a true gentleman.

1:52:44.097 --> 1:52:45.766
You're delusional.

1:52:46.475 --> 1:52:47.601
And you've killed millions.

1:52:47.684 --> 1:52:49.061
(CLICKS)

1:52:49.144 --> 1:52:51.939
What say one more,
for good measure?

1:52:52.731 --> 1:52:53.732
Hey!

1:52:58.487 --> 1:52:59.571
(GROANS)

1:53:00.447 --> 1:53:01.740
(YELLING)

1:53:05.077 --> 1:53:06.578
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1:53:26.974 --> 1:53:28.183
(YELLS)

1:53:30.185 --> 1:53:32.354
(CHUCKLING) Come on, old man.

1:53:32.437 --> 1:53:34.022
-(GROANS)
-Get up.

1:53:35.148 --> 1:53:36.608
I said, get up!

1:53:48.662 --> 1:53:50.163
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1:54:42.633 --> 1:54:44.092
(GROANS)

1:54:58.273 --> 1:55:00.943
Fuck this gentleman shite.

1:55:14.331 --> 1:55:15.832
(GOATS BLEATING)

1:55:18.627 --> 1:55:19.837
(GROANS)

1:55:24.967 --> 1:55:26.385
Fuck's sake.

1:55:32.057 --> 1:55:33.350
(GRUNTING)

1:55:33.433 --> 1:55:35.310
You bastard.

1:55:35.394 --> 1:55:37.229
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1:56:02.296 --> 1:56:04.131
(SCREAMING)

1:56:12.097 --> 1:56:15.976
Give my regards
to dear old Kitch, yeah?

1:56:17.019 --> 1:56:18.645
(SCREAMING)

1:56:23.025 --> 1:56:24.234
(BLEATS)

1:56:24.318 --> 1:56:25.569
(YELLING)

1:56:34.536 --> 1:56:37.456
You can't do it.
You can't let me fall.

1:56:37.748 --> 1:56:39.875
It goes against your every belief.

1:56:39.958 --> 1:56:42.461
You are a pacifist.

1:56:43.337 --> 1:56:45.839
(IN ENGLISH ACCENT)
And I'm now completely reliant

1:56:45.923 --> 1:56:47.341
on your mercy, old boy.

1:56:47.508 --> 1:56:50.969
You're right. I shouldn't let you fall.

1:56:51.386 --> 1:56:56.475
Only now I have become the man
that my son would have been.

1:56:59.895 --> 1:57:01.730
You... (SCREAMING)

1:57:08.070 --> 1:57:09.905
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1:57:30.217 --> 1:57:31.218
Sir.

1:57:31.593 --> 1:57:33.470
Shola, are you all right?

1:57:34.471 --> 1:57:36.598
We've been through worse, Your Grace.

1:57:38.016 --> 1:57:40.769
So, you'd jump
in front of a bullet for me,

1:57:40.853 --> 1:57:42.688
but not out of an airplane?

1:57:44.231 --> 1:57:45.899
So it would seem. (CHUCKLES)

1:57:47.150 --> 1:57:48.527
Thank you, my friend.

1:57:48.694 --> 1:57:50.153
My pleasure.

1:57:51.905 --> 1:57:53.657
-So, Shola.
-Hmm?

1:57:54.074 --> 1:57:56.618
How are we going
to get down from here?

1:58:09.256 --> 1:58:10.674
PRESIDENT WILSON: Come in.

1:58:11.341 --> 1:58:14.678
Mr. President, Chef has made
your favorite peanut butter cookies.

1:58:19.933 --> 1:58:21.310
Thank you.

1:58:37.451 --> 1:58:38.660
Oh...

1:58:39.161 --> 1:58:42.122
Get me the generals, immediately.

1:58:46.418 --> 1:58:48.670
We're goin' to war!

1:58:52.549 --> 1:58:54.551
(ALL CHEERING)

1:59:04.770 --> 1:59:08.357
KING GEORGE:
This victory is all down to you

1:59:08.524 --> 1:59:11.527
and your fine son, Conrad.

1:59:11.902 --> 1:59:14.988
And the courage
of so many others, sir.

1:59:15.155 --> 1:59:16.490
Of course.

1:59:18.116 --> 1:59:20.869
Britain thanks you. And I thank you

1:59:21.203 --> 1:59:23.372
for ensuring that
I didn't meet the same fate

1:59:23.455 --> 1:59:24.706
as my cousins.

1:59:25.749 --> 1:59:28.544
<i>Wilhelm's abdication
was understandable,</i>

1:59:29.753 --> 1:59:31.755
<i>but what happened to Nicholas...</i>

1:59:32.631 --> 1:59:33.715
(WOMAN SCREAMS)

1:59:34.633 --> 1:59:36.093
...was despicable.

1:59:36.260 --> 1:59:37.886
It was, sir.

1:59:38.053 --> 1:59:39.847
I owe you a great personal debt

1:59:39.930 --> 1:59:41.932
that I still have my crown.

1:59:44.518 --> 1:59:46.019
In that case,

1:59:46.103 --> 1:59:49.690
would you meet me tomorrow
at Kingsman, 3:00?

1:59:49.857 --> 1:59:51.942
-A tailor shop?
-Yes, sir.

1:59:52.109 --> 1:59:54.778
Number 11, Savile Row.

1:59:59.992 --> 2:00:03.245
All of us here today are united,

2:00:03.328 --> 2:00:07.040
sadly, in losing
our sons and friends

2:00:07.207 --> 2:00:09.251
in this terrible war.

2:00:09.334 --> 2:00:12.171
What happened to this
generation of young men

2:00:12.254 --> 2:00:14.173
must never happen again.

2:00:14.423 --> 2:00:17.634
I believe the terms
of Versailles are too onerous,

2:00:17.801 --> 2:00:22.139
too extreme, and could
precipitate another war.

2:00:22.306 --> 2:00:25.058
What the world needs
is an organization

2:00:25.142 --> 2:00:26.435
that can channel its resources

2:00:26.518 --> 2:00:30.981
towards preserving peace
and protecting life.

2:00:31.148 --> 2:00:33.984
An independent
intelligence agency

2:00:34.151 --> 2:00:37.154
operating at the highest level
of discretion,

2:00:37.321 --> 2:00:39.573
above the politics and bureaucracy

2:00:39.656 --> 2:00:42.701
of government-run spy organizations.

2:00:43.452 --> 2:00:44.703
To that end,

2:00:45.537 --> 2:00:48.540
I have acquired this shop.

2:00:48.707 --> 2:00:53.629
And I propose that we become
the founding members of

2:00:54.296 --> 2:00:56.965
the Kingsman agency.

2:00:58.634 --> 2:01:00.552
My code name will be...

2:01:02.304 --> 2:01:03.430
Arthur.

2:01:03.972 --> 2:01:05.390
And if you agree to join me,

2:01:05.474 --> 2:01:06.975
you may turn over your place card,

2:01:07.142 --> 2:01:09.603
where you will find
your own code name.

2:01:12.356 --> 2:01:14.399
I am Galahad.

2:01:15.317 --> 2:01:16.610
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

2:01:18.487 --> 2:01:19.947
I am Lancelot.

2:01:21.573 --> 2:01:24.368
I am Bedivere.

2:01:27.663 --> 2:01:29.623
I am Percival.

2:01:29.790 --> 2:01:30.874
Excellent.

2:01:32.167 --> 2:01:35.254
And this is Merlin,

2:01:35.420 --> 2:01:38.382
who will be our quartermaster.

2:01:39.299 --> 2:01:42.678
May our sons and friends
rest in peace.

2:01:43.011 --> 2:01:46.265
And long live the Kingsman.

2:01:47.599 --> 2:01:49.434
ALL: The Kingsman.

2:02:10.914 --> 2:02:12.791
<i>Your body</i>

2:02:12.875 --> 2:02:16.628
<i>Moves like a river
through a house of stone</i>

2:02:17.588 --> 2:02:19.298
<i>So softly</i>

2:02:19.381 --> 2:02:22.926
<i>Like a shadow never comes undone</i>

2:02:24.386 --> 2:02:26.680
<i>You can never know</i>

2:02:26.763 --> 2:02:30.475
<i>Your destiny</i>

2:02:30.559 --> 2:02:33.395
<i>Or what the mirror shows you</i>

2:02:33.478 --> 2:02:37.232
<i>Isn't real</i>

2:02:37.316 --> 2:02:40.402
<i>Only you can</i>

2:02:40.485 --> 2:02:43.363
<i>Truly understand</i>

2:02:43.447 --> 2:02:47.701
<i>The measure of a hero</i>

2:02:47.784 --> 2:02:53.457
<i>Is the measure of a man</i>

2:02:54.625 --> 2:03:01.089
<i>The measure of a man</i>

2:03:02.299 --> 2:03:04.009
<i>Nobody</i>

2:03:04.092 --> 2:03:07.721
<i>Sees the man behind the face you show</i>

2:03:08.722 --> 2:03:10.474
<i>Nobody</i>

2:03:10.557 --> 2:03:14.061
<i>Feels the burden that is yours alone</i>

2:03:15.562 --> 2:03:17.731
<i>You can never know</i>

2:03:17.814 --> 2:03:21.568
<i>Your destiny</i>

2:03:22.027 --> 2:03:24.696
<i>Or what the mirror shows you</i>

2:03:24.780 --> 2:03:28.534
<i>Isn't real</i>

2:03:28.617 --> 2:03:31.745
<i>Only you can</i>

2:03:31.828 --> 2:03:34.873
<i>Truly understand</i>

2:03:34.957 --> 2:03:39.586
<i>The measure of a hero</i>

2:03:39.670 --> 2:03:46.176
<i>Is the measure of a man</i>

2:03:47.719 --> 2:03:50.722
Now it's time to address
the balance of my new flock.

2:03:50.806 --> 2:03:53.350
Thanks to you, Comrade,
our left hand is strong.

2:03:53.517 --> 2:03:54.768
But as you once said,

2:03:54.852 --> 2:03:56.854
our right hand
now needs strengthening.

2:03:56.937 --> 2:03:58.272
(BANGING ON DOOR)

2:03:58.355 --> 2:03:59.648
Come in.

2:04:00.023 --> 2:04:01.441
(DOOR OPENS)

2:04:05.112 --> 2:04:06.363
Don't be shy.

2:04:06.780 --> 2:04:07.948
Come, come.

2:04:12.452 --> 2:04:13.453
My Shepherd.

2:04:14.121 --> 2:04:16.206
This young man will come to rival

2:04:16.290 --> 2:04:18.625
your position in this world, my friend.

2:04:19.710 --> 2:04:21.837
It is an honor, Comrade Lenin.

2:04:23.922 --> 2:04:25.591
And your name?

2:04:27.342 --> 2:04:29.052
Adolf Hitler.
